    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>Hellgleam is a material found in areas where the land is steeped in fiendish (usually Devil-aligned) energies. Perpetually warm to the touch and very hard to smelt down once its settled to the ingot, Hellgleam equipment perform strongly against cold-aligned creatures and celestials.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Weapons: </strong>Hellgleam Weapons deal additional damage to creatures weak to Hellgleam, which are typically Celestials. In addition, Strikes made with Hellgleam trigger weaknesses to Fire damage; a weapon with Hellgleam gains the Fire trait.</li>\n<li><strong>Armor:</strong> Hellgleam Armor is imbued with the warmth of fire and protects you from celestial entities. You are protected from severe cold while wearing Hellgleam Armor, and as a reaction to a Strike from a creature weak to Hellgleam, you can grant yourself a +1 circumstance bonus to your AC.</li>\n<li><strong>Shields</strong>: Hellgleam shields ignite and often give a reflective glow. When you Raise a Shield, the shield sheds bright light in a 20-foot radius and dim light to the next 20 feet.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Hellgleam Items</h2>\n<table style=\"width:380px;user-select:text;color:#191813;font-size:13px;height:314px\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">\n<tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;height:17px\">\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;color:white;height:32px;width:219px;background-color:#522e2c;text-align:center\">\n<h3><strong>Hellgleam Items</strong></h3>\n</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;color:white;width:74px;text-align:center;background-color:#522e2c;height:32px\">\n<h3><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><strong>Hardness</strong></strong></h3>\n</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;color:white;width:41px;text-align:center;background-color:#522e2c;height:32px\">\n<h3>HP</h3>\n</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;color:white;width:45px;text-align:center;background-color:#522e2c;height:32px\">\n<h3>BT</h3>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;height:17px\">\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;height:25px;width:219px;text-align:center;background-color:#f6f1e1\"><strong>Thin Items</strong></td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;width:74px;text-align:center;background-color:#f6f1e1;height:25px\"> </td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;width:41px;text-align:center;background-color:#f6f1e1;height:25px\"> </td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;width:45px;text-align:center;background-color:#f6f1e1;height:25px\"> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;height:17px\">\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;height:25px;width:219px;background-color:#eee5c8;text-align:center\">Low-grade</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;width:74px;text-align:center;background-color:#eee5c8;height:25px\">3<span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;display:block\"></span></td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;width:41px;text-align:center;background-color:#eee5c8;height:25px\">12</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;width:45px;text-align:center;background-color:#eee5c8;height:25px\">6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;height:17px\">\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;height:25px;width:219px;text-align:center;background-color:#f6f1e1\">Standard-grade</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;width:74px;text-align:center;background-color:#f6f1e1;height:25px\">5</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;width:41px;text-align:center;background-color:#f6f1e1;height:25px\">20</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;width:45px;text-align:center;background-color:#f6f1e1;height:25px\">10<